properties.Title: Wind Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Strong winds that may cause damage are expected or occurring. A low pressure system tracking through the central Prairies this weekend will bring strong northwesterly winds to southern Saskatchewan beginning overnight and persisting through Sunday. These gusty northwesterly winds will be strongest in Kindersley, Leader, and Swift Current with gusts in excess of 90 km/h beginning Sunday morning. The strong winds will gradually diminish Sunday evening. ### Damage to buildings, such as to roof shingles and windows, may occur. High winds may toss loose objects or cause tree branches to break. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to SKstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #SKStorm.
